==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wily
<hw>Wil"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Wilier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Wiliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From <er>Wile</er>.]</ety>
<def>Full of wiles, tricks, or stratagems; using craft or stratagem to
accomplish a purpose; mischievously artful; subtle.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Wily</xex> and wise.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>wily</xex> snake.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This false, <qex>wily</qex>, doubling disposition of mind.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Cunning; artful; sly; crafty. See
<er>Cunning</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wimble</ent>⟦br⟧
